uses that is the problem?

00:44:47.750 --> 00:44:50.160
And if it's not and
if there's more

00:44:50.160 --> 00:44:52.330
than downstream licensed
uses that are the problem,

00:44:52.330 --> 00:44:53.900
let's say Richard
Prince for example,

00:44:53.900 --> 00:44:55.880
although I think he is the
exception rather than the rule,

00:44:55.880 --> 00:44:58.360
where will there
been an instance

00:44:58.360 --> 00:45:03.660
of an attribution controversy
that is not also an infringement

00:45:03.660 --> 00:45:10.140
of the rights of copyright and
remediable from that avenue?

00:45:10.140 --> 00:45:13.020
&gt;&gt; Brad A. Greenberg:
Any takers?

00:45:13.020 --> 00:45:14.800
&gt;&gt; Paul Alan Levy:
I mean certainly

00:45:14.800 --> 00:45:21.360
to the extent particularly when
you're dealing outside the range

00:45:21.360 --> 00:45:27.640
of form contracts with a
huge commercial enterprises

00:45:27.640 --> 00:45:31.640
with which a creator is
dealing, a writings requirement

00:45:31.640 --> 00:45:33.890
and an explicit writings
requirement

00:45:33.890 --> 00:45:37.620
at least provides a point
of discussion and sort

00:45:37.620 --> 00:45:41.450
of conscious giving
up or conscious taking

00:45:41.450 --> 00:45:46.990
and I think requirements of
clear and unmistakable waiver,

00:45:46.990 --> 00:45:50.490
for example, play a large
role in many areas of law

00:45:50.490 --> 00:45:52.530
and I think they're valuable.

00:45:54.040 --> 00:45:57.740
&gt;&gt; Eugene Mopsik: Just
