00:47:55.610 --> 00:48:00.100
of a better word amateur users
who are using the web just

00:48:00.100 --> 00:48:03.010
like the big commercial players.

00:48:03.010 --> 00:48:04.180
And so we have to think

00:48:04.180 --> 00:48:09.550
about how accessible the
legislation would be to use.

00:48:09.550 --> 00:48:12.380
&gt;&gt; Eugene Mopsik: Yeah, we're
not chasing the amateurs.

00:48:12.380 --> 00:48:13.660
&gt;&gt; Jane Ginsburg: If
it's not inappropriate,

00:48:13.660 --> 00:48:16.360
I'd like to venture an
answer to the question,

00:48:16.360 --> 00:48:21.200
which is one big difference is
between an infringement action

00:48:21.200 --> 00:48:23.610
and a moral rights action is

00:48:23.610 --> 00:48:26.940
if the authors doesn't have
the economic rights any more,

00:48:26.940 --> 00:48:28.950
the author doesn't have
an infringement action

00:48:28.950 --> 00:48:31.910
but the author could is still
have a moral rights action.

00:48:31.910 --> 00:48:33.040
&gt;&gt; Nancy E. Wolf: Good point.

00:48:33.040 --> 00:48:33.340
&gt;&gt; Jane Ginsburg: And I'd

00:48:33.340 --> 00:48:37.380
like to make another suggestion
regarding downstream uses

00:48:37.380 --> 00:48:39.790
which may require
legislation but I have to think

00:48:39.790 --> 00:48:43.240
about if you could do it
without legislation which is,

00:48:43.240 --> 00:48:46.450
as Nancy says, nobody wants
to go after downstream users.

00:48:46.450 --> 00:48:48.220
But what about the platforms?

00:48:48.220 --> 00:48:54.370
Could there been a 512 type
claim based on attribution?

00:48:54.370 --> 00:48:59.050
So in other words if there's
no attribution on the content

00:48:59.050 --> 00:49:03.080
that has been placed
on the platform,

00:49:03.080 --> 00:49:06.560
that would be the basis
to either have it taken

00:49:06.560 --> 00:49:09.560
down or attribution added.

00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:13.450
So that might be a way
of rendering enforceable

00:49:13.450 --> 00:49:15.740
and attribution right
which is distinct

00:49:15.740 --> 00:49:17.960
from the economic right.

00:49:17.960 --> 00:49:20.140
&gt;&gt; Nancy E. Wolf: And if there
