I mean many years
ago I did photographs

00:51:06.610 --> 00:51:10.250
of the lighted Ben Franklin
bridge in Philadelphia

00:51:10.250 --> 00:51:13.580
and the architect calls me
up and he had the opportunity

00:51:13.580 --> 00:51:17.010
to license these images
to use for his purposes

00:51:17.010 --> 00:51:19.920
and when he found, you know,
I give him the fees for it

00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:22.350
and he didn't want to pay.

00:51:22.350 --> 00:51:24.320
He didn't want to do anything.

00:51:24.320 --> 00:51:26.500
Well, then two years
later I get a call

00:51:26.500 --> 00:51:31.020
from AIA they're giving this
man some life achievement award

00:51:31.020 --> 00:51:33.460
and they want to use
my photographs as part

00:51:33.460 --> 00:51:35.790
of the presentation
thanking him.

00:51:35.790 --> 00:51:37.970
And so I said you know
he had the opportunity

00:51:37.970 --> 00:51:40.760
to license these images
and he turned it down.

00:51:40.760 --> 00:51:42.930
I said what do you
have in your budget

00:51:42.930 --> 00:51:46.630
to use this image in
your presentation?

00:51:46.630 --> 00:51:48.710
And they said well we
don't have any money

00:51:48.710 --> 00:51:50.980
